<p>North Hills and Midtown represent prime locations for solar installations, with many newer homes featuring south-facing roof orientations and minimal shading. These upscale neighborhoods often have larger homes exceeding 2,500 square feet, making 8-10kW solar systems common. The established tree canopy in areas like Hayes Barton and Oakwood requires careful solar site assessment, though mature neighborhoods often have the highest electricity usage due to older, less efficient homes requiring system upgrades.</p>

<p>Newer developments in Brier Creek and Falls of Neuse offer excellent solar potential with modern roof designs and planned orientations. These areas frequently feature homes with high-efficiency HVAC systems already installed, making them ideal candidates for solar-plus-storage solutions. Downtown and warehouse district condos present unique opportunities for shared solar programs, while suburban areas like Cary and Apex (technically outside Raleigh but served by similar utilities) show strong adoption rates for both solar and high-efficiency heat pump systems.</p>

